#show: template

#taxon[Example]
#title[Morphism of schemes]

Let $X = PP_k^(1)$, $Y = "Spec" k$

$
  pi: X -> Y
$

The map between topological spaces is the constant map (to the zero ideal). It is trivially continous. 
The structure sheaf of $"Spec" k$ at ${<<0>>}$ is $k$ and at empty sets its $0$.

For the morphism of sheaves $pi^(hash)$, give $pi^hash$ on $V$ by $k -> k$ restricted to $V$ or $0$ if $V$ is empty.

